# Build Phase 1: File Pointer to Mux Asset

## Question

Build the proof pipeline in `joelclaw-video`, registered through system-bus: an event (working name `video/publish.requested`) carrying a flagg filesystem path triggers an Inngest function that validates the file, creates a Mux direct upload with the audited asset settings (progressive rendition; captions come from the Deepgram ticket, not Mux auto-gen), PUTs the bytes, then correlates the already-routed mux webhook events (`upload.asset_created` → `asset.ready`) to land asset id + playback id, emitting `video/publish.completed` and failing loud on `asset.errored`. Durability posture matches the rest of system-bus: idempotency-keyed on file checksum or upload id, steps retryable, no silent failures. Record the video through joelclaw-api's mutations (`createVideo`, `patchFromMuxWebhook`) — the [charter](./charter-joelclaw-api.svx) fixed strict sequencing (custody → api mutations → this build), the stash-and-backfill fallback is retired, and defining the video mutations in joelclaw-api per [the model](./model-video-resource-in-convex.svx) is this build's first step. Mux credentials go through agent-secrets like every other provider. Resolved when a real screen recording on flagg goes in and a playing `player.mux.com/<PLAYBACK_ID>` URL comes out, with the run visible in Inngest. The resolution records the event contracts — the agent-surface and watch-page tickets depend on them.
